offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-one"][vc_accordion_tab title="What kind of equipment do you use to train?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We use free weights, Rogue strength and conditioning equipment, Bosu ball, medicine balls, battle ropes, resistance bands, and many different training equipment to help you reach your goals and overall strength.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What happens if I can't make my appointment ?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]If you miss your appointment for whatever reason, please give your trainer a 24-hour notice. A Late Cancel charge of $15 will occur if you cancel within 12 hours of a class start time. Otherwise it will be considered a "NO-SHOW" which means you pay full for that session. If you're late, please text/or notify your trainer. Your trainer may give you a workout plan you can finish on your own. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Can I Move My Reservation ?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]If you need to move your appointment but there is less than 12 hours until your scheduled class, that would be considered a cancellation and the above cancellation policy would apply. Sorry, no exceptions.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What are your payment policies?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]All class purchases are non-transferable, non-refundable, non-extendable. All monthly unlimited packages start on the date of first use. All monthly contracts are signed for auto renewal for each month or can be paid in full up front. [/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What payment method do you accept?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]To keep everything convenient, we accept credit cards for personal training sessions and group classes. We have a merchant account set up and keep your credit card on file and take out dues automatically through EFT (electronic funds transfer) through your financial institution. If you decide to cancel your training or put your training on hold, please give us a 15-day notice so you will not be charged for the following month.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Does move-sf have an open gym membership?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Unfortunately, move-sf does not have an open gym membership, so there is no monthly membership option/fee. move-sf is a private, boutique facility offering personal training, small group classes, seminars/workshops, and an in house Physical Therapist: action sports medicine.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Where do I park for havnor?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]2 hour metered and 2 hour non-metered street parking is available around havnor. It can be difficult at times, so please plan accordingly. We encourage people to walk, cycle (parking inside the gym), take public transportation (move-sf is on the 1 California and 24 Divisadero Muni routes), or take a car service to the facility.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][/vc_accordion][/vc_column][vc_column offset="vc_col-lg-6 vc_col-md-6"][vc_accordion accordion_style="style-one"][vc_accordion_tab title="How much does personal training cost?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]All of the trainers at move-sf are independent, and set their own rates. Prices for packages of 5 sessions or more range from $90 per session to $150 per session depending on the trainer. Email info@move-sf.com for more information.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Are there initiation fees?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]No, we believe that once you join AW, youll be hooked for life. Were a family owned business, and you wont experience hidden fees and up sells.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Do you run female only workshops?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]No We foster an inclusive atmosphere where all ages, genders and beliefs are accepted equally. Training with a diverse group leads to a more holistic fitness experience for all.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Is there a discount if I refer a friend?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We run referral promotions year round so you are definitely rewarded for introducing your friends to HAVNOR![/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="Whats included in the nutrition session?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]Our nutrition specialists have formulated a broad range of healthy meal options to sustain appropriate energy levels while keeping you looking fit and healthy.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="How the phoenix effect compare to other workouts?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]On the whole, traditional gyms do not get you functionally fit, most group exercise studios miss the mark in high-level programming, online and DVD workouts lack coaching, and CrossFit lacks the quality control to be safe for general populations. Most corporate gym classes are one-off workouts that may feel good at first, but are unlikely to produce long-term results. Many other group exercise studios rely on gimmicks and false promises to get you in the door, and do not produce lasting change and improvements.[/vc_column_text][/vc_accordion_tab][vc_accordion_tab title="What is the recommended level of fitness?" sub_title="Sub Title 1"][vc_column_text]We welcome people of all ages, shapes, sizes, and fitness levels!
